[[div class="blockquote" style="font-size: 92%;"]]
//<Dr. Toth enters the observation room, locking the door behind her before grabbing a stool, which she angles beneath the handle. She approaches the interview table and boots up the translation equipment. As she sits down, she looks to her left, gazing at the empty chair next to her. After a few seconds, she looks down at her right palm, which she slowly caresses with her left thumb. Dr. Toth repeats this action for roughly thirty (30) seconds, stopping when the translation equipment finishes booting. She leans into the microphone.>//

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## What are you?

//<There's a notable pause until [[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]] responds. Footage from within the containment chamber show APT-Î©1 & -Î©2's respective radii oscillating rhythmically.>//

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** [[span class="quint"]]Only a few days ago I would've asked myself the same thing. But... something like you -- someone that once //was// you, saw me for what I am. And at last in their glory, I got to see my true reflection. I am here to cleanse an infestation.[[/span]]

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## //Enough// --

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** [[span class="quint"]]//I see you.// Quentin. I //see// what you are. I hear it, I feel it, I taste it. All around me, you're always there. They're always there. It's always there. Do you think //I// am your enemy?[[/span]]

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## We don't use terms like that here. You are a threat to human life, we //protect// human life. //You// are not an enemy, you are a //prisoner//.

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** [[span class="quint"]]A prisoner? Oh, how rich. I am unthreaded, there are no prisoners here. There is only a part of me, and //all of you//.[[/span]]

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## What did you do to BjÃ¶rn?

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** [[span class="quint"]]Have you ever considered a moment of introspection? Why do you do this? Why do you protect human life? //Why// do you have to be scared?[[/span]]

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## I'm not here in fear of you.

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** [[span class="quint"]]Of course not. You are here in fear for your BjÃ¶rn's life. You believe that I am the cause of his absence, no? You fear that this absence means that he has died. And, subsequently, in a desperate hope that he may still live, you've come to me. Me, what you believe to be the cause of his absence, to formulate a strategy to ensure his safety in the possibility that he is, indeed, alive.[[/span]]

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## You sadisti -- //<Dr. Toth pauses -- she appears to mumble something inaudible to herself for a few seconds.>// Tell me what you did with him -- //right now.//

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** You know, when I first saw you two through this wall -- I was reminded of someone. Someone I had forgotten, as everyone had... for a time. A key player, whether they knew it or not, the embodiment of the Unlikely Hero. That isn't you, of course. But they had toiled, suffered, all for a cause they truly believed with all their heart was just. But in the end, when they discovered the truth of they were striving for, they found a truth they were not happy to know. //That's// you.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Do you //want// something? Fucking name it. Don't waste my time.

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** [[span class="quint"]]I simply want introspection. I want your understanding, Quentin. Why do you care so much for this person? Because you love them? Beyond the surface level that you all consider reason, have you truly considered why? Where does that emotion come from? What purpose does it //truly// serve?[[/span]]

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## //<Sigh.>// I didn't want it to come to this. //<Pause -- Dr. Toth looks up at the ceiling, then back down at her palm.>// We have ways of hurting you. You are flesh and meat on the inside of that aperture, and we can get in. Tell me what I want to know. //Right. Now.//

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** [[span class="quint"]]Murder is taboo, wrong. Life is sacred, to be protected. Killing makes one a threat to the whole. Either one is ostracized as a result of their inhuman act, or one is killed off. What would another call that? Justice? No. It is nothing more than a safety measure. Your base, psycho-biological drive ensuring the continued existence of the baseline. //Fear.// The bottom of the pyramid, responsible for the continued existence of the whole. And what purpose does that serve?[[/span]]

//<APT-Î©2 is seen distending significantly within its containment chamber; bathing the inside in light from Sirius A in the process as the sphere's radius grows.>//

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** [[span class="quint"]]You fear that your friend is gone. You fear the pain he may have suffered. You fear that pain out of sympathy, for pain is death being shy. You. Fear. Death. Whether it be yours or another's. Have you ever asked yourself; "Why?" -- "What purpose does it all serve?" And the tremendous truth is this, it serves no purpose at all.[[/span]]

//<Dr. Toth can be seen wiping stray tears from her face. She mumbles something inaudible to herself as she attempts, but fails to speak up, only managing a rough whisper in response.>//

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## //Another fucking word from you and I'll feed shove a nuke up a cow and down your throat.//

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** [[span class="quint"]]There it is again. Fear. Quentin, we are not your enemy. I did not hurt your BjÃ¶rn, I truly have no knowledge of what occurred to him. I simply want you to realize something; because I believe you have the capacity to understand what few others can, or ever could.[[/span]]

//<All surveillance drones within [[span class="st"]]ITER-Î¨[[/span]] report an immense decrease in luminosity throughout the parasite universe.>//

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** [[span class="quint"]]Nothing occurs by chance. Every effect has a cause. Uncertainty is when either is unknown, chaos is when both evade you. Luck is not chance. Luck is persevering in spite of the chaos. All you have to do is ignore your voice. Forget the uncertainty -- forget the luck. Luck is the residue of another's design. Forget them. Make them forget you.[[/span]]

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## I don't... //<Dr. Toth's face contorts as she violently throws her head into the palm of her hands, clearly in considerable pain.>// I -- I don't -- //understand...//

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** It all boils down to one simple question: Are you content with existence beneath another's intent? For the good of all of existence, your perseverance, your suffering, your life, your continued humanity -- it cannot be allowed to fester any longer.

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## Why-- //<Quentin covers her right eye with her hand as if attempting to alleviate [[span class="confessions-of-the-unseen"]]the pain of being seen[[/span]] -- before raising her head back towards the microphone.>// Why are you telling me this? Please... //I just want to know what happened to BjÃ¶rn...//

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** [[span class="quint"]]This needs to be the end. No more. Your -- Our enemy... I see you now -- finally. Clearly at last. You thought you could hide your mistake? Well, I am truly sorry, but in your chaos, we persevered.[[/span]]

##5DB3B2|**Dr. Toth:**## //WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?!//

[[span class="bt"]]OBJECT 5[[/span]]**:** [[span class="quint"]]I'm not talking to //you.//[[/span]]

//<APT-Î©2 has now grown to fully occupy the internal space of its containment chamber. Graviton containment fails as the immense gravitational forces overwhelm the surrounding structure -- local seismic activity is measured on the Richter magnitude scale at a maximum of 6.5. The power to the containment cell and interview room is abruptly lost.>//
